  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposal, by reason of its size and position would result in the obstruction of light and outlook to a residential window which would result in an unacceptable adverse impact on the amenity of the residential occupiers. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies D1 (London’s form, character and capacity for growth) and D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP3 (Development and Amenity) and LP7 (Advertisements) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020).",
    "The proposed advertisement, by virtue of its scale, design and positioning, would harm the visual amenity of the&amp;nbsp; character and appearance of the host building, a Building of Townscape Merit and the Broadway Market Conservation Area. As such the proposal is contrary to policies D1 (London’s form, character and capacity for growth), D8 (Public Realm) and HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) of the London Plan 2021 and policies LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) and LP7 (Advertisements) of the Hackney Local Plan LP33 2020"
  ],
